+# Codex Compatibility
+
+## Purpose
+
+Codex should treat Pala Memory Core as an evidence-first local control system.
+
+## How Codex Should Work In This Repo
+
+Codex should make small scoped changes, collect command evidence, and report the result without hiding warnings or generated outputs.
+
+## Branch Discipline
+
+Use a feature branch for each change. Do not push directly to `main`.
+
+## PR Discipline
+
+Open a draft PR for review, keep the changed-file scope explicit, and wait for owner approval before merge.
+
+## Smoke Discipline
+
+Run the relevant smoke commands before claiming a task is complete:
+
+- `python -m py_compile pala.py`
+- `python pala.py doctor`
+- `python pala.py token intel`
+- `python pala.py source court`
+- `python pala.py dashboard export --all`
+- `python pala.py list --limit 10`
+
+## Evidence Discipline
+
+Use command output, PR metadata, CI checks, and release court comments as evidence.
+
+## Forbidden Actions
+
+Do not create releases, tags, force pushes, generated runtime commits, secret commits, pricing UI, upgrade UI, subscription UI, billing UI, trial UI, or paywall UI.
+
+## Generated Files
+
+Generated files stay local and ignored unless the owner explicitly approves otherwise.
+
+## Source Court
+
+External packages, MCP servers, SDKs, and imported source ideas must pass Source Court before becoming implementation dependencies.
+
+## Token Intelligence
+
+Token Intelligence classifies repository intake before large reads and keeps local context low-noise.
+
+## Dashboard Work
+
+Dashboard changes must preserve free local mode, owner approval, evidence ledger, token intelligence, source court, and no-paywall language.
+
+## Report Format
+
+Reports should include verdict, files changed, commands run, evidence, problems found, remaining risks, and next mission.
+
+## Recovery / Resume
+
+On resume, inspect branch, status, PR state, CI, and generated-file hygiene before continuing.
+
+## Next Steps
+
+Keep this protocol stable while v0.19 receives owner review.
